The retained PSRC dump has seven HLSL asset shaders with the exact `pow(saturate(dot(...)), materialSpecularPower)` form among the 17 dumped programs, including `a_specmap_pp_ps20.psh`. One more important nuance: the source guards the `pow()` behind `if (dot3DiffuseIntensity > 0)`, but your disassembly still reaches the `pow` with `N.H == 0`; that means the trigger is not “all back-facing pixels,” it is “diffuse-lit pixels whose half-angle dot is zero while power is zero.”
